      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Needs maintainer/security policy review and contributor real-run proof before automation can safely help; the diagnostic gap is concrete but not the only blocker.; Needs attention: The diff changes which local directory can supply prompt instructions and safety rules, so the trust-boundary change needs maintainer approval and proof.; Review finding: [P2] Pass the default agent id into bootstrap diagnostics —... (sha=8df20895874a199152aa84368f71028b19b0c348)",
      "review_summary": "The PR changes `src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` so explicitly configured `agentDir` bootstrap files are merged with workspace bootstrap files and same-named `agentDir` files take precedence.\n\nPR surface: Source +30. Total +30 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. by source inspection: current main loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir` only and does not read configured `agentDir`. I did not run a live setup in this read-only review.",
