      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): load bootstrap files from agentDir alongside workspace",
        "body": "## Problem\n`src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir` only and does not read explicitly configured `agentDir`. When users configure an `agentDir` for their agents, bootstrap files placed there are ignored.\n\nFixes #29387\n\n## Root Cause\n`loadBootstrapFiles()` only queries `workspaceDir` and the `agentDir` config path was never passed into the loader.\n\n## Fix\nModify `loadBootstrapFiles()` to also load explicitly configured `agentDir` bootstrap files, with `agentDir` files overriding same-named workspace files. Gate loading on explicit `agentDir` config to avoid unnecessary file I/O. Filter `BOOTSTRAP.md` from both directories.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Agent bootstrap files placed in configured `agentDir` were silently ignored; only `workspaceDir` bootstrap files were loaded.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux (Node.js 22), openclaw development checkout with pnpm, vitest 4.1.8.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `node ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-core.config.ts src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n```\n$ node ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-core.config.ts src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/user/openclaw\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  37 passed (37)\n   Start at  10:58:08\n   Duration  3.71s (transform 2.03s, setup 676ms, import 2.35s, tests 376ms, environment 0ms)\n```\n- **Observed result after fix**: All 37 bootstrap-files tests pass, including agentDir bootstrap loading, same-name override precedence, BOOTSTRAP.md filtering, and gated-on-explicit-config behavior.\n- **What was not tested**: End-to-end agent bootstrap with a live agent directory on disk was not manually tested. The tests cover the loader behavior in isolation with mocked file system paths.",
